Reports unused path variables in Kotlin router DSL as well as usages of undeclared path variables.
<p>
  Path variables must be declared in the route path before access.
  Attempt to access an undeclared path variable will result in a runtime error.
</p>

<p><b>Example:</b></p>
<pre><code>
@Configuration
class RouterConfiguration {
    @Bean
    fun myRouter() = router {
        GET("/test/{var}") { ServerResponse.ok().body("${it.pathVariable("bar")}") }
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p><b>After the fix is applied:</b></p>
<pre><code>
@Configuration
class RouterConfiguration {
    @Bean
    fun myRouter() = router {
        GET("/test/{var}") { ServerResponse.ok().body("${it.pathVariable("var")}") }
    }
}
</code></pre>
